column17: Madison Square Garden split into two publicly traded companies in October. MSG owns the sports teams (Rangers, Knicks, Liberty) and buildings (Madison Square Garden, Radio City Music Hall, The Forum in L.A.). MSG Networks owns the regional sports networks (MSG, MSG+). The enterprise value of MSG as of November was $2.96 billion. The Rangers and Knicks signed a 20-year contract extension with MSG to broadcast the teams' games.

They have not won the Stanley Cup since 1993, but the Canadiens are still the most popular brand in the NHL north of the border. According to a poll for CityNews last year, the Habs were the most cheered-for team in Canada with 23% support, versus 12% for both the Maple Leafs and Canucks. Although Montreal is a much smaller market than Toronto, the Canadiens television audience is often 20% greater than the Leafs when you include both the English and French language channels.
